28static const char ALPHABET[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ-. $/+%abcd*";
29
30/**
31* These represent the encodings of characters, as patterns of wide and narrow bars.
32* The 9 least-significant bits of each int correspond to the pattern of wide and narrow.
33*/
34static const int CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[] = {
35 0x114, 0x148, 0x144, 0x142, 0x128, 0x124, 0x122, 0x150, 0x112, 0x10A, // 0-9
36 0x1A8, 0x1A4, 0x1A2, 0x194, 0x192, 0x18A, 0x168, 0x164, 0x162, 0x134, // A-J
37 0x11A, 0x158, 0x14C, 0x146, 0x12C, 0x116, 0x1B4, 0x1B2, 0x1AC, 0x1A6, // K-T
38 0x196, 0x19A, 0x16C, 0x166, 0x136, 0x13A, // U-Z
39 0x12E, 0x1D4, 0x1D2, 0x1CA, 0x16E, 0x176, 0x1AE, // - - %
40 0x126, 0x1DA, 0x1D6, 0x132, 0x15E, // Control chars? $-*
41};
42
43static_assert(Size(ALPHABET) - 1 == Size(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS), "table size mismatch");
44
45static const int ASTERISK_ENCODING = CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[47];
46
47static int AppendPattern(std::vector<bool>& target, int pos, int a)
48{
49 for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
50 int temp = a & (1 << (8 - i));
51 target[pos + i] = temp != 0;
52 }
53 return 9;
54}
55
56
57static int ComputeChecksumIndex(const std::string& contents, int maxWeight)
58{
59 int weight = 1;
60 int total = 0;
61
62 for (int i = Size(contents) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
63 int indexInString = IndexOf(ALPHABET, contents[i]);
64 total += indexInString * weight;
65 if (++weight > maxWeight) {
66 weight = 1;
67 }
68 }
69 return total % 47;
70}

73ZXING_EXPORT_TEST_ONLY
74std::string Code93ConvertToExtended(const std::wstring& contents)
75{
76 size_t length = contents.length();
77 std::string extendedContent;
78 extendedContent.reserve(length * 2);
79
80 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
81 int character = contents[i];
82 // ($)=a, (%)=b, (/)=c, (+)=d. see Code93Reader.ALPHABET
83 if (character == 0) {
84 // NUL: (%)U
85 extendedContent.append("bU");
86 }
87 else if (character <= 26) {
88 // SOH - SUB: ($)A - ($)Z
89 extendedContent.push_back('a');
90 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + character - 1));
91 }
92 else if (character <= 31) {
93 // ESC - US: (%)A - (%)E
94 extendedContent.push_back('b');
95 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + character - 27));
96 }
97 else if (character == ' ' || character == '$' || character == '%' || character == '+') {
98 // space $ % +
99 extendedContent.push_back(character);
100 }
101 else if (character <= ',') {
102 // ! " # & ' ( ) * ,: (/)A - (/)L
103 extendedContent.push_back('c');
104 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + character - '!'));
105 }
106 else if (character <= '9') {
107 extendedContent.push_back(character);
108 }
109 else if (character == ':') {
110 // :: (/)Z
111 extendedContent.append("cZ");
112 }
113 else if (character <= '?') {
114 // ; - ?: (%)F - (%)J
115 extendedContent.push_back('b');
116 extendedContent.push_back((char)('F' + character - ';'));
117 }
118 else if (character == '@') {
119 // @: (%)V
120 extendedContent.append("bV");
121 }
122 else if (character <= 'Z') {
123 // A - Z
124 extendedContent.push_back(character);
125 }
126 else if (character <= '_') {
127 // [ - _: (%)K - (%)O
128 extendedContent.push_back('b');
129 extendedContent.push_back((char)('K' + character - '['));
130 }
131 else if (character == '`') {
132 // `: (%)W
133 extendedContent.append("bW");
134 }
135 else if (character <= 'z') {
136 // a - z: (*)A - (*)Z
137 extendedContent.push_back('d');
138 extendedContent.push_back((char)('A' + character - 'a'));
139 }
140 else if (character <= 127) {
141 // { - DEL: (%)P - (%)T
142 extendedContent.push_back('b');
143 extendedContent.push_back((char)('P' + character - '{'));
144 }
145 else {
146 throw std::invalid_argument(std::string("Requested content contains a non-encodable character: '") + (char)character + "'");
147 }
148 }
149 return extendedContent;
150}
151
152BitMatrix
153Code93Writer::encode(const std::wstring& contents_, int width, int height) const
154{
155 std::string contents = Code93ConvertToExtended(contents_);
156
157 size_t length = contents.length();
158 if (length == 0) {
159 throw std::invalid_argument("Found empty contents");
160 }
161 if (length > 80) {
162 throw std::invalid_argument("Requested contents should be less than 80 digits long after converting to extended encoding");
163 }
164
165 //lenght of code + 2 start/stop characters + 2 checksums, each of 9 bits, plus a termination bar
166 size_t codeWidth = (contents.length() + 2 + 2) * 9 + 1;
167
168 std::vector<bool> result(codeWidth, false);
169
170 //start character (*)
171 int pos = AppendPattern(result, 0, ASTERISK_ENCODING);
172
173 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
174 int indexInString = IndexOf(ALPHABET, contents[i]);
175 pos += AppendPattern(result, pos, CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[indexInString]);
176 }
177
178 //add two checksums
179 int check1 = ComputeChecksumIndex(contents, 20);
180 pos += AppendPattern(result, pos, CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[check1]);
181
182 //append the contents to reflect the first checksum added
183 contents += static_cast<wchar_t>(ALPHABET[check1]);
184
185 int check2 = ComputeChecksumIndex(contents, 15);
186 pos += AppendPattern(result, pos, CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[check2]);
187
188 //end character (*)
189 pos += AppendPattern(result, pos, ASTERISK_ENCODING);
190
191 //termination bar (single black bar)
192 result[pos] = true;
193
194 return WriterHelper::RenderResult(result, width, height, _sidesMargin >= 0 ? _sidesMargin : 10);
195}
